title: Dunfermline 4-0 Forfar: Match Report
text:
Dunfermline 4-0 Forfar: Match Report 24 Oct 2015 16:31:00 
comments Dunfermline stay top of Scottish League One with 4-0 rout of ForfarDunfermline held their place at the summit of Scottish League One with a convincing 4-0 win at home to struggling Forfar. The East End Park side were quickly out of the traps, taking the lead inside 10 minutes. Michael Moffat cut through the Bairns' defence with a determined run, and squared for David Hopkirk to apply a simple finish.Joe Cardle doubled the lead, pouncing swiftly when Rob Douglas dropped an Andy Geggan cross.Ryan Wallace took a Shaun Byrne pass in his stride before dispatching the third.The same player completed the scoring in the last 10 minutes, this time netting with his left foot to extend Forfar's winless run.
